<li class="wordpress odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 social-comment social-clearfix social-wordpress" id="li-comment-31">
<div class="social-comment-inner social-clearfix" id="comment-31">
	<div class="social-comment-header">
		<div class="social-comment-author ">
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=80&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo avatar-default' height='40' width='40' /><cite class="social-fn fn"><a href='http://donotremove.net' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Phelps</a></cite>		</div>
		<!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		<div class="social-comment-meta social-comment-meta-wordpress">
			<span class="social-posted-from">
								<span>View</span>
							</span>
			<a href="http://werblog.com/2005/07/tell-me-again-why-the-mac-is-better/#comment-31" class="social-posted-when" target="_blank">July 5, 2005</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="social-comment-body">
				<p>Just to be clear &#8212; I have to force quit sometimes, but I almost never have to restart.  (I have had two since getting Tiger, though, and that is wierd.)</p>
	</div>
			<div class="social-actions entry-meta">
			</div>
		<!-- .reply -->
</div><!-- #comment-31 -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
<li class="wordpress even thread-even depth-1 social-comment social-clearfix social-wordpress" id="li-comment-32">
<div class="social-comment-inner social-clearfix" id="comment-32">
	<div class="social-comment-header">
		<div class="social-comment-author ">
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=80&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo avatar-default' height='40' width='40' /><cite class="social-fn fn">Kevin Werbach</cite>		</div>
		<!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		<div class="social-comment-meta social-comment-meta-wordpress">
			<span class="social-posted-from">
								<span>View</span>
							</span>
			<a href="http://werblog.com/2005/07/tell-me-again-why-the-mac-is-better/#comment-32" class="social-posted-when" target="_blank">July 5, 2005</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="social-comment-body">
				<p>I get the impression that Tiger (even 10.4.1, which I have) is still buggy and not yet really ready for prime time.  I&#8217;m hoping that explains some of the problems I&#8217;m having.  I haven&#8217;t had another hard crash requring a restart, so maybe I&#8217;ll find better stability than Windows after all.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m loathe to call warranty service, which is bound to be a time suck, but I may be forced to if I can&#8217;t get the USB drives working.  I use keychain drives all the time to transfer files.  Now that I&#8217;ve moved all my files over, I also can&#8217;t afford to give up the machine for any length of time.</p>
